      "message": "Issue #2: Test Logic Flaw - LDAP Configuration Does Not Affect Local User Operations\n\nLocation: Lines 545-604 in redfish/account_service/test_ldap_configuration.robot\nIssue: The test configures an unreachable LDAP server, then performs local user operations (create user, change privilege, verify permissions). However, LDAP configuration has no impact on local user operations. Local users are stored in the BMC\u0027s local database and are completely independent of LDAP configuration. This test would pass identically whether LDAP is configured, misconfigured, or not configured at all.\n\nWhy: This is a critical test design flaw. The test appears to validate that \"local admin operations work when LDAP is down,\" but this is always true by design - local authentication is independent of LDAP. The test provides no meaningful validation beyond what a basic local user test would provide.\nWhat makes this a logic flaw:\n\nThe LDAP configuration step (lines 554-556) is irrelevant to the rest of the test\nLines 67-104 test local user operations that work regardless of LDAP state\nThe test creates false confidence that it\u0027s validating LDAP-related behavior when it\u0027s not\n\nFix Required: Either:\n\nRemove the LDAP configuration entirely and make this a pure local user test\nOR add meaningful LDAP-specific validation, such as:\n\nVerify LDAP users cannot login when server is unreachable\nVerify local users CAN login when LDAP is unreachable (failover scenario)\nVerify LDAP authentication resumes after restoring LDAP configuration\nTest the interaction between LDAP and local authentication\n\n\nRecommended approach:\n\n```\nVerify Local Admin Failover When LDAP Server Unreachable\n    [Documentation]  Verify that local admin authentication continues to work\n    ...  when LDAP server becomes unreachable, ensuring BMC remains accessible.\n    [Tags]  Verify_Local_Admin_Failover_When_LDAP_Server_Unreachable\n    \n    # First verify LDAP authentication works with valid configuration.\n    Redfish.Login  ${LDAP_USER}  ${LDAP_USER_PASSWORD}\n    Redfish.Logout\n    \n    # Configure LDAP with unreachable server.\n    Create LDAP Configuration  ${LDAP_TYPE}  ${LDAP_UNREACHABLE_URI}\n    ...  ${LDAP_BIND_DN}  ${LDAP_BIND_DN_PASSWORD}  ${LDAP_BASE_DN}\n    Sleep  15s\n    \n    # Verify LDAP authentication fails.\n    ${ldap_login_status}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n    ...  Redfish.Login  ${LDAP_USER}  ${LDAP_USER_PASSWORD}\n    Should Be Equal  ${ldap_login_status}  ${False}\n    ...  msg\u003dLDAP user was able to login with unreachable LDAP server.\n    \n    # CRITICAL: Verify local admin can still login (failover).\n    Redfish.Login  ${OPENBMC_USERNAME}  ${OPENBMC_PASSWORD}\n    \n    # Verify local admin can perform management operations.\n    Redfish Create User  ${LOCALTESTUSER}  ${TEST_USER_PASSWORD}  Administrator  ${True}\n    Verify User Role  ${LOCALTESTUSER}  Administrator\n    \n    # Verify newly created local user can login.\n    Redfish.Logout\n    Redfish.Login  ${LOCALTESTUSER}  ${TEST_USER_PASSWORD}\n    Redfish.Logout\n    \n    # Restore LDAP and verify LDAP authentication resumes.\n    Redfish.Login\n    Restore LDAP URL\n    Sleep  15s\n    Redfish.Logout\n    \n    # Verify LDAP authentication works again.\n    Redfish.Login  ${LDAP_USER}  ${LDAP_USER_PASSWORD}\n    Redfish.Logout\n```",
