      "message": "Issue #3: Hard-coded Sleep Duration Without Justification\n\nLocation: Line 556 in redfish/account_service/test_ldap_configuration.robot\nIssue: The test uses Sleep 15s after configuring LDAP with an unreachable server. Hard-coded sleep durations are fragile and can cause flaky tests or unnecessary delays.\n\nFix: Replace with a more robust wait mechanism or add a comment explaining why 15 seconds is necessary. Consider using a retry loop with timeout instead.\nWhy: Hard-coded sleeps make tests slower and less reliable. If the system responds faster, time is wasted. If it responds slower, the test may fail intermittently.\n\nSuggested improvement:\n\n# Wait for LDAP configuration to be applied (timeout mechanism would be better).\nSleep  15s\nOr better yet, implement a wait-and-verify pattern:\n\n```\n# Wait for LDAP configuration to propagate.\nWait Until Keyword Succeeds  30s  5s\n...  Verify LDAP Configuration Applied  ${LDAP_UNREACHABLE_URI}\n```",
